- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper shows that finding the optimal attribute hiding scheme is NP-hard and proposes heuristic-based schemes. This involves algorithmic techniques and may be relevant to the sub-category of DS.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper deals with a probabilistic auction model and proposes revenue-maximizing strategies. This involves statistical and machine learning techniques and may be relevant to the sub-category of LG.
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses the scenario of a website hiding certain attributes of its impressions, which may be related to multimedia content (e.g., images, videos) and their associated attributes. This may be relevant to the sub-category of MM.
